	<center>
            <h1>Private message confidentiality</h1>
            <hr>
	</center>
	<ul>
            <li>Currently, private messages are broadcast to every client and filtered on the client side</li>
            <li>Malicious (or even merely curious) user may monitor TCP packets and easily discern the content of private messages</li>
            <li>Private messages are also written into transcripts</li>
            <p>Users may not be aware they are sending private communications when providing transcripts to others.</p>
	</ul>
</body>
